repository-code: https://github.com/khaledyusuf44/somali-corpus
url: https://huggingface.co/datasets/khaledyusuf44/somaliweb-v1
abstract: >-
  SomaliWeb v1 is the first dedicated, versioned, documented Somali pretraining
  corpus: 819,322 documents and approximately 303 million tokens, aggregated
  from HPLT v2, CC100, and Somali Wikipedia, then passed through a six-stage
  reproducible pipeline (byte-exact dedup, mojibake repair, language-ID
  verification, MinHash + LSH near-dedup at Jaccard tau = 0.80, character-5-gram
  quality filtering, BPE-16K tokenizer training). The release ships with a
  matched BPE-16K tokenizer that is 40.2% more token-efficient than GPT-4's
  cl100k_base on FLORES-200 Somali devtest, and the first public per-class
  Somali language-identification benchmark across langdetect, GlotLID v3, and
  fastText lid.176.
keywords:
  - Somali
  - low-resource NLP
  - pretraining corpus
  - language identification
  - tokenizer fertility
  - MinHash
  - deduplication
  - Horn of Africa
  - African NLP
